name: Wild Strawberry
keyFeatures: Small white 5-petaled flowers|Bright red berries with seeds on outside|Three-leaflet compound leaves|Low growing plant
lookAlikes: Mock strawberry (yellow flowers, tasteless fruit)|Indian strawberry (similar)
preparation: Eat berries fresh when ripe|Leaves can be dried for tea|Harvest when bright red
warnings: Avoid plants near roadsides|Make sure berries are truly ripe
medicinal: Leaves traditionally used for digestive tea|Vitamin C source
traditional: Folk remedy for stomach ailments|Dye from berries
ethics: Only take what you need|Leave plenty for wildlife|Don't uproot plants
funFacts: Wild strawberries are much smaller but more flavorful than cultivated ones!
